# TBQC Gia Pha — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Flask web app for managing a Vietnamese royal family tree (Nguyen Phuoc Toc).
Backend: Python 3 + Flask. Database: MySQL. Deploy: Render/Railway.

## Project Structure
- `app.py` — Single entry point. Must be run from repo root: `python app.py`
- `blueprints/` — Flask blueprints: main, auth, activities, family_tree, persons, members_portal, gallery, admin
- `folder_py/` — Utility modules: db_config, genealogy_tree. NOT an entry point.
- `templates/` — Jinja2 HTML templates
- `static/` — CSS (`static/css/`), JS, images (`static/images/`)
- `scripts/` — Dev/ops utilities (backup, route listing, etc.)

## Key Rules

### Running the app
- Always run `python app.py` from the **repo root**, never from `folder_py/` or any subdirectory.
- Local dev: requires `.env` file (see `.env.example`). Never commit `.env`.

### Environment Variables
All secrets go in `.env` (local) or platform dashboard (Render/Railway). Never hardcode:
- `SECRET_KEY`, `DB_HOST`, `DB_USER`, `DB_PASSWORD`, `DB_NAME`, `DB_PORT`
- `MEMBERS_PASSWORD`, `ADMIN_PASSWORD`, `BACKUP_PASSWORD`
- `GEOAPIFY_API_KEY`

### Database
- MySQL via `mysql-connector-python`. Connection config in `folder_py/db_config.py`.
- Use `get_db_config()` from `folder_py.db_config` to get connection params.
- Never hardcode DB credentials anywhere in source code.

### Security
- No SQL injection: always use parameterized queries with `%s` placeholders.
- No XSS: escape user content in templates (Jinja2 auto-escapes by default).
- Passwords hashed with `bcrypt`. Never store plaintext passwords.
- Rate limiting via `Flask-Limiter` on sensitive endpoints.
- CORS restricted to allowed origins (see `app.py`).

### Code Style
- Python 3, follow PEP 8.
- Keep blueprints focused — one concern per blueprint.
- Vietnamese comments are acceptable (project uses mixed Vietnamese/English).
- Avoid over-engineering: minimal changes, no premature abstraction.

### Dependencies (requirements.txt)
flask, flask-cors, mysql-connector-python, bcrypt, flask-login, gunicorn,
requests, beautifulsoup4, lxml, Pillow, openai, anthropic, flask-wtf,
Flask-Limiter, Flask-Caching, python-dotenv, pandas, openpyxl

### Gitignore (do NOT commit these)
`.env`, `*.env`, `.cursor/`, `folder_sql/`, `tailieu/`, `backups/`, `*.sql`,
`*.csv`, `static/documents/*.pdf`, `create_*_admin*.py`

## Debugging
- Health check: `GET /api/health` — shows `blueprints_registered` status.
- If `/genealogy`, `/members`, `/contact` return 404 after deploy: check Start Command is `python app.py` at repo root.
- Startup log "OK: Da dang ky Flask Blueprints." = blueprints loaded OK.
